ibis.ipl
Class IbisStarter

java.lang.Object
  ibis.ipl.IbisStarter

public abstract class IbisStarter
extends Object

Every Ibis implementation must provide an IbisStarter which is used by the Ibis factory to check capabilities, port types, and to start an Ibis instance. This class is not to be used by Ibis applications. Ibis applications should use IbisFactory to create Ibis instances.

matches

public abstract boolean matches(IbisCapabilities capabilities,
                                PortType[] portTypes)

Parameters:
capabilities - the required capabilities.
portTypes - the required port types.
Returns:
true if it can.

isStacking

public boolean isStacking()
Decides if this Ibis instance is a stacking Ibis.

Returns:
true if it is stacking.

isSelectable

public abstract boolean isSelectable()
Returns true if this starter can be used to automatically start an Ibis (without the user specifying an implementation). An Ibis implementation can exclude itself from the selection mechanism by having this method return false.

Returns:
true if this starter can be used in the selection mechanism.

unmatchedIbisCapabilities

public abstract CapabilitySet unmatchedIbisCapabilities()
Returns the required capabilities that are not matched by this starter. Note: a stacking Ibis returns the capabilities that are required of the underlying Ibis implementation. This call must be preceded by a call to matches(IbisCapabilities, PortType[]).

Returns:
the unmatched ibis capabilities.

unmatchedPortTypes

public abstract PortType[] unmatchedPortTypes()
Returns the list of port types that are not matched by this starter. If all required port types match, this method returns an array with 0 elements. Note: a stacking Ibis returns the porttypes that are required of the underlying Ibis implementation. This call must be preceded by a call to matches(IbisCapabilities, PortType[]).

Returns:
the unmatched port types.

startIbis

public Ibis startIbis(List<IbisStarter> stack,
                      RegistryEventHandler handler,
                      Properties userProperties)
Actually creates a stacking-ibis instance from this starter.

Parameters:
stack - the starters for the underlying ibis implementations. The last element of the list should be a starter for a non-stacking ibis.
handler - a registry event handler.
userProperties - the user properties.
